File: Vodacom said it has identified and remedied a fault with a core network element at one of its sites. BackpagePix/Richard Huggard JOHANNESBURG - For the second time in 10 days, Vodacom customers have been left without a network connection. The company, in a short response, said it has identified and remedied a fault with a core network element at one of its sites. Vodacom experienced a similar outage on 13 November. It blamed that on simply 'an issue' without giving details about what went wrong. At the time, Vodacom recommended that users switch their flight mode on and off and restart their devices.